data.text: 3/31: Hit the protein goal, touch over the calorie goal, but still doing well. https://t.co/MuVF2h5WJk
@DelphiDoggo Fibre/fiber is your friend.  Helps reduce the gas you can get from all that protein, and especially from protein shakes.

Day 2/31:
Didn't quite reach my protein goal, just didn't really fancy chugging another protein shake just to reach it. And since i want to lose weight, I'd rather be a bit under than a bit over. https://t.co/ngIGB4W8Fk

@DelphiDoggo For most weekday lunches, I reward myself with a bag of crisps once I’ve forced my way through a raw carrot, an apple, some tomatoes, and whatever else will push me over 5-a-day. It’s not the most fun but I’ve been doing it for about 15 years and it gets the fibre in for sure.

Well day 1 and I've done a decent job of hitting my macro and calorie goals.
